text.section:
A member of a limited liability company does not manage the business and affairs of the limited liability company under subsection (g) of this section solely by doing one or more of the following:
Consulting with or advising the individuals who manage the business and affairs of the limited liability company;
Directing the management of the limited liability company in the same manner as a director of a corporation directs the management of a corporation; or
Voting on any matter required to be voted on by the members of the limited liability company, including but not limited to:
The approval or disapproval of amendments to the operating agreement;
The termination and winding up of the limited liability company;
The sale, exchange, lease, mortgage, pledge, or other transfer of a material portion of the assets of the limited liability company;
The incurring of indebtedness by the limited liability company other than in the ordinary course of its business;
A change in the nature of the business of the limited liability company;
The expulsion or admission of a member;
The appointment or discharge of a manager;
The merger of the limited liability company with or into any other entity; or
Any matter related to the business of the limited liability company not otherwise enumerated in this subsection that the operating agreement states may be subject to the approval or disapproval of the members.

section.section:
A dealer or other person liable for the tax imposed by this subtitle may not:
Willfully fail to collect the tax;
Willfully fail to remit the tax;
Willfully make any false statement or misleading omission with regard to the tax;
Willfully fail to keep records in accordance with this subtitle and any regulations pursuant to this subtitle; or
Willfully evade payment of the tax by any means.
